==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Landau
<hw>Lan"dau</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the town
<etsep>Ladau</etsep> in Germany; cf. F. <ets>landau</ets>. See
<er>Land</er>, <er>Island</er>.]</ety> <def>A four-wheeled covered
vehicle, the top of which is divided into two sections which can be let
down, or thrown back, in such a manner as to make an open
carriage.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>landaw</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Landaulet</ent>⟦br⟧
